{"id": 231992234, "title": "Josh Maravich, 'Pistol' Pete's son, dead at 42", "text": "Josh Maravich, the son of the Hall of Famer \"Pistol\" Pete, died last week. He was 42. Josh, like his father, played basketball at LSU \u2013 he didn't quite have his father's stardom, playing in only 13 games. However, it was a childhood dream for him to play at the arena that bears his father's name. CLICK HERE FOR MORE SPORTS COVERAGE ON FOXNEWS.COM \"I wanted to come here for my dad to make him proud,\" Josh said in a 2005 article in the LSU school paper, The Daily Reveille, per the university's site. \"I knew I wasn\u2019t going to be a star player, but for me being a walk-on was what I always wanted to do.\" The school said he died in his family's home in Covington, Louisiana. Pistol Pete was back in the news earlier this year, as Caitlin Clark surpassed his NCAA record for the most points ever scored by a college basketball player. CAITLIN CLARK SNUBBED FROM OLYMPIC ROSTER PARTLY DUE TO POTENTIAL BACKLASH OVER LIMITED PLAYING TIME: REPORT In his three years in Baton Rouge, Pistol Pete scored 3,667 points \u2013 Clark surpassed him by 284. He was the third overall pick in the 1970 NBA Draft to the Atlanta Hawks, and he was a five-time NBA All-Star. Pete retired after the 1979-1980 season, but post-retirement life was short \u2013 he died in 1988 at the age of 40 due to a heart condition that went undetected. No cause of death has been given for Josh. Josh was just 5 years old when his father died. Josh is survived by his mother, Jackie, stepfather James, and older brother Jaeson. CLICK HERE TO GET THE FOX NEWS APP The Maravich brothers were both involved in the statue ceremony for their father, coming up with the idea that he should be shown with a vintage behind-the-back pass. Follow Fox News Digital\u2019s sports coverage on X, and subscribe to the Fox News Sports Huddle newsletter.", "summary": "Josh Maravich, the son of Hall of Fame basketball player &quot;Pistol&quot; Pete, died on Friday at rhe age of 42, his alma mater in LSU announced.", "url": "https://www.foxnews.com/sports/josh-maravich-pistol-petes-son-dead-42", "image": "https://a57.foxnews.com/static.foxnews.com/foxnews.com/content/uploads/2024/06/931/523/Josh-Maravich.jpg?ve=1&tl=1", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 13:52:53", "author": "Ryan Morik", "authors": ["Ryan Morik"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.06}